oc:kn_00672fed a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding on gating strategy for a free tool" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For lead capture, prefer partial gating: give enough free value to demonstrate worth, then gate the detailed/actionable output behind email. Minimal friction (email only), show preview of gated content." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Partial gating balances maximum reach/SEO value with meaningful lead capture, outperforming both fully gated (too much friction) and fully ungated (no leads)." .

oc:kn_03dcabfc a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating any free tool concept" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The free tool must solve a real problem the audience actually has, provide genuine value, and be useful even without the core product. It must be adjacent to what you sell with a natural path from tool to product." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A tool that doesn't solve a real problem won't get used or shared; adjacency ensures the tool attracts the right audience and creates a natural conversion path." .

oc:kn_5f600a1b a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any tool strategy discussion" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Check for .agents/product-marketing-context.md (or .claude/product-marketing-context.md) first. Read it before asking questions to leverage existing context about the product, audience, and positioning." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Avoids redundant questions and ensures strategy is grounded in the user's actual product context." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_adc04edf a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assessing tool viability" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The tool must pass the investment test: lead value × expected leads > build cost + ongoing maintenance cost." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Free tools have hidden costs in maintenance; without positive ROI, the tool becomes a drain rather than an asset." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_d0bc2384 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When comparing or validating tool ideas" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use the 8-factor evaluation scorecard (search demand, audience match, uniqueness, path to product, build feasibility, maintenance burden, link-building potential, share-worthiness). Score 25+/40 = strong candidate, 15-24 = promising, <15 = reconsider." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Provides a structured, quantitative way to compare tool concepts and avoid sunk cost on weak ideas." .

oc:kn_d50e016a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scoping the initial tool build" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never build an overly complex MVP. Skip account creation, saving results, advanced features, perfect design, and edge case handling initially." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Over-building delays launch, increases maintenance burden, and delays learning whether the concept actually attracts leads." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

